Next Meeting of FMC Data Initiative Engages FedEx, UPS, and Amazon

Posted February 18, 2022

The next meeting of the Federal Maritime Commission Maritime Transportation Data Initiative will be held on:

Date: Tuesday, February 22, 2022

Time: 3:00-4:00 PM (Eastern Time)

The meeting is open to the public and can be viewed online via a link provided here prior to the meeting.

Commissioner Carl W. Bentzel is leading this initiative at the direction of Chairman Daniel B. Maffei.

Scheduled Participants:

  • Cynthia Allen-Vice President Regulatory Affairs & Compliance, FedEx Logistics
  • Steve McMichael-Vice President, UPS Ocean
  • Adnan Quadri-Director, Global Imports-Network Planning and Infrastructure, Amazon
